{
  "texts": [
    "It is highly effective for detecting anomalies in network traffic.",
    "Random Forest combines the predictions of multiple decision trees, each trained on a different subset of the data.",
    "To classify an instance, each decision tree casts a \"vote, \" and the class with the most votes becomes the predicted class.",
    "For anomaly detection, Random Forest typically uses an \"outlier score\" based on the proportion of trees that classify an instance as an anomaly.",
    "Figure 11 shows the decision boundary."
  ]
}